headline: FSLR Q2 Deep Dive: U.S. Policy Tailwinds Offset International Headwinds and Margin Compression
summary: Solar panel manufacturer First Solar (NASDAQ:FSLR) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 8.6% year on year to $1.10 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $5.3 billion at the midpoint came in 4.2% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $3.18 per share was 19.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
